instructions: Lie down on a flat bench with your feet firmly on the ground.
Grip the barbell with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Lower the barbell to your chest, keeping your elbows at a 45-degree angle from your body.
Push the barbell back up until your arms are fully extended.
Place the barbell on your upper back, gripping it with hands wider than shoulder-width apart.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and toes pointing slightly outward.
Lower your body by bending your knees and pushing your hips back.
Push through your heels to return to the starting position.
Stand with your feet hip-width apart and the barbell over your mid-foot.
Bend your knees and hips to lower your body and grip the barbell with an overhand or mixed grip.
Keep your back straight and chest up as you lift the barbell off the ground by extending your hips and knees.
Lower the barbell back to the ground by bending your knees and hips.
Grip a pull-up bar with your hands shoulder-width apart and palms facing away from your body.
Hang from the bar with your arms fully extended and feet off the ground.
Pull your body up by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Lower your body back down to the starting position.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell at your collarbone level with your palms facing forward.
Press the barbell overhead by extending your arms.
Pause for a moment at the top, then lower the barbell back to the starting position.
Sit on the lat pulldown machine and adjust the thigh pad to secure your legs.
Grip the bar with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and palms facing away from your body.
Pull the bar down to your upper chest by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Slowly extend your arms to return the bar to the starting position.
Sit on the pec deck machine facing the back pad and adjust the seat height so the handles are at shoulder level.
Grip the handles with your palms facing inward and elbows slightly bent.
Pull the handles back by squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Slowly return to the starting position.
Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Grip the bar with your palms facing up and arms fully extended.
Curl the handle toward your chest by bending your elbows.
Slowly return to the starting position.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an overhand grip.
Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at your hips, keeping your back straight.
Pull the barbell toward your lower chest by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position.
Sit on the pec deck machine with your back against the pad.
Place your forearms on the padded levers, with your elbows at a 90-degree angle.
Push the levers together by squeezing your chest muscles.
Slowly return to the starting position.
Grip the parallel dip bars with your palms facing inward and arms straight.
Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the ground.
Push through your palms to return to the starting position.
Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Grip the handle with your palms facing down and elbows bent at a 90-degree angle.
Push the handle down by extending your elbows until your arms are straight.
Slowly return to the starting position.
Lie down on an incline bench with your feet firmly on the ground.
Hold a dumbbell in each hand at chest level, with your palms facing away from your body.
Press the dumbbells up until your arms are fully extended.
Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position.
Stand with your feet hip-width apart and hold a barbell with an overhand grip.
Keeping your back straight and knees slightly bent, hinge forward at your hips to lower the barbell.
Push through your heels to return to the starting position.
Sit on the leg press machine with your back against the pad and feet on the platform.
Adjust the seat so that your knees form a 90-degree angle.
Push through your heels to extend your legs and move the platform away from your body.
Slowly return to the starting position.
Sit on the leg extension machine with your back against the pad.
Place your ankles under the padded lever, adjusting the machine as needed.
Extend your legs by pushing against the padded lever.
Slowly return to the starting position.
Lie face down on the hamstring curl machine with your knees just off the edge of the pad.
Place your ankles under the padded lever, adjusting the machine as needed.
Curl your legs toward your glutes by bending your knees.
Slowly return to the starting position.
Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart.
Step forward with one foot and lower your body until your front knee is at a 90-degree angle.
Push through your front heel to return to the starting position and repeat on the other side.
Begin in a high plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and feet hip-width apart.
Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor.
Push through your hands to return to the starting position.
Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart.
Raise your heels off the ground by pushing through the balls of both feet.
Lower your heels back to the ground and repeat.
Lie on your back and place your hands behind your head.
Lift both legs off the ground and extend one while bringing the opposite knee towards your chest.
Simultaneously rotate your torso so your opposite elbow moves toward the lifted knee.
Alternate sides.
Sit at a cable row station with your feet on the platform and knees slightly bent.
Grasp the cable handle and pull it towards your waist while keeping your back straight.
Extend your arms to return the handle to the starting position.
Get into a high plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and feet hip-width apart.
Ensure your body forms a straight line from your head to your heels.
Hold this position for the desired length of time.
Lie on a flat bench holding two dumbbells directly above your chest with your palms facing each other.
With a slight bend at your elbows, lower the weights to the side of your body in a wide arc.
Stop when your elbows are in line with your shoulders.
Use your chest to reverse the action and bring the weights back up to the start position.
Lie on your back on the floor with a barbell above your chest and your hands gripping the bar wider than shoulder-width apart.
Keep your feet flat on the floor and your knees bent to 90 degrees.
Lower the bar towards your chest until your upper arms touch the floor.
Pause, then push the bar back to the starting position, fully extending your arms.
Lie on a bench and hold a barbell with your hands shoulder-width apart.
Lower the bar to your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body.
Press the bar back to the starting position.
Repeat the process.
Lie down on a decline bench and grip the bar slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Lower the bar to your chest, keeping your elbows at 45 degrees.
Press the bar back up to the starting position.
Repeat the process.
Lie on a flat bench holding two dumbbells directly above your chest with your palms facing each other.
With a slight bend at your elbows, lower the weights to the side of your body in a wide arc.
Stop when your elbows are in line with your shoulders.
Use your chest to reverse the action and bring the weights back up to the start position.
Lie on your back on the floor with a barbell above your chest and your hands gripping the bar wider than shoulder-width apart.
Keep your feet flat on the floor and your knees bent to 90 degrees.
Lower the bar towards your chest until your upper arms touch the floor.
Pause, then push the bar back to the starting position, fully extending your arms.
Lie down on the bench underneath the Smith machine.
Position the bar in line with your chest.
Unrack the bar, lower it to your chest, keeping your elbows at 45 degrees.
Press the bar back up to the starting position.
Repeat the process.
Sit on the chest press machine with your back flat against the pad.
Grip the handles with your palms facing down and elbows at 90 degrees.
Push the handles away from you, fully extending your arms.
Return the handles back to the starting position and repeat.
Stand tall with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing towards your body.
Keeping your arms straight, raise the dumbbells in front of you until they are at shoulder height.
Pause briefly, then lower the weights back to your sides.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell in front of your body with an overhand grip.
Pull the barbell straight up towards your chin, leading with your elbows.
Lower the bar back to the starting position and repeat.
Stand upright with a dumbbell in each hand at your sides, palms facing in.
Keeping your back straight, lift the dumbbells out to your sides until they reach shoulder level, while keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Lower the dumbbells back down to your sides.
Stand upright with a dumbbell in each hand at your sides, palms facing in.
Keeping your back straight, lift the dumbbells out to your sides until they reach shoulder level, while keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Lower the dumbbells back down to your sides.
Bend forward at the waist while keeping your back flat.
Hold a dumbbell in each hand with palms facing in.
Raise your arms out to the sides until they are in line with your shoulders.
Lower the dumbbells back down and repeat.
Bend forward at the waist while keeping your back flat.
Hold a dumbbell in each hand with palms facing in.
Pull the dumbbells up towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body.
Lower the dumbbells back down and repeat.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell at shoulder level, palms facing forward.
Press the barbell straight up until your arms are fully extended.
Lower the barbell back to shoulder level and repeat.
Attach a rope to a cable machine and adjust it to your eye level.
Grab the ends of the rope with each hand and step back to create tension.
Pull the rope towards your face, spreading it apart and squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Return to the starting position and repeat.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell at shoulder level, palms facing forward.
Press the barbell straight up until your arms are fully extended.
Lower the barbell back to shoulder level and repeat.
Stand straight holding a dumbbell in front of your chest with both hands.
Keeping your arms straight, raise the weight to eye level and hold for a few seconds.
Lower the weight slowly back to your chest and repeat.
Start with your feet shoulder-width apart, and hold a barbell in front of your shoulders with an overhand grip.
Dip your body by bending your knees, then explosively push up with your legs as you press the barbell over your head.
Under the barbell quickly and catch it with arms fully extended.
Lower the barbell back to your shoulders and repeat.
Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, feet shoulder-width apart.
Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back flat.
Raise the dumbbells out to the sides, squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position and repeat.
Sit on a bench with back support, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder level.
Push the dumbbells up until your arms are fully extended.
Slowly lower the dumbbells back to shoulder level and repeat.
Sit on a bench with back support, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder level.
Push the dumbbells up until your arms are fully extended.
Slowly lower the dumbbells back to shoulder level and repeat.
Sit on a bench with back support, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder level.
Push the dumbbells up until your arms are fully extended.
Slowly lower the dumbbells back to shoulder level and repeat.
Stand with a dumbbell in each hand, feet shoulder-width apart.
Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back flat.
Raise the dumbbells out to the sides, squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Lower the dumbbells back to the starting position and repeat.
Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, arms fully extended, and palms facing your torso.
Keep your elbows close to your torso and curl the weights while keeping the palms facing each other.
Continue to raise the weight until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level.
Lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position.
Sit on a preacher bench and place your arms on the support pad.
Grip the barbell with an underhand grip and fully extend your arms.
Curl the weight up, keeping your arms on the pad, until your biceps are fully contracted.
Lower the weight back to the starting position.
Stand up straight, holding a cable rope attached to the low pulley, palms facing up.
Curl your hands towards your biceps, keeping your palms up and elbows close to your body.
Slowly return to the starting position and repeat.
Sit on a flat bench with your feet firmly on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in your right hand, palm facing upward.
Lean forward, resting your right elbow against the inside of your right knee, letting the weight hang down between your legs.
Curl the weight up, keeping your elbow against your knee.
Lower the weight back to the starting position and repeat.
Adjust the seat of the machine so that your upper arms rest comfortably on the pad.
Grab the handles with palms facing upwards.
Curl your arms, lifting the weight as you squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement.
Slowly return to the starting position and repeat.
Position yourself facing down on an incline bench with your chest and stomach press against the incline pad.
Hold the barbell with an underhand grip and let your arms hang straight down.
Curl the weight up, squeezing your biceps at the top.
Lower the weight back to the starting position and repeat.
Stand up straight holding a dumbbell with both hands, and lift it over your head until both arms are fully extended.
Keep your elbows in while slowly lowering the weight behind your head as you bend your elbows.
Lift the weight back up by extending your arms and repeat.
Lie on a flat bench holding a barbell with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart, and press it vertically upward.
Keeping your upper arms still, lower the bar by bending your elbows until it almost touches your forehead.
Extend your arms back to the starting position and repeat.
Place your hands shoulder-width apart on a bench or step behind you.
Extend your legs out in front of you.
Lower your body by bending at the elbows until you're at about a 90-degree angle.
Push back up to the start position and repeat.
Stand facing away from a high pulley with a rope attached.
Reach up and grab the rope with both hands, and bend at the hips until your torso is about a 45-degree angle to the floor.
Keeping your upper arms close to your head, extend your elbows to straighten your arms.
Slowly return to the starting position and repeat.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and a barbell held behind your legs.
Bend your knees and lower your body into a squat, keeping your back straight.
Push through your heels to return to the starting position and repeat.
Stand upright with your hands at your hips.
Take a step forward with one foot and lower your body until your front knee is at a 90-degree angle and your back knee is hovering above the floor.
Push back up to the starting position and repeat with the other leg.
Stand upright with your hands at your hips.
Take a step forward with one foot and lower your body until your front knee is at a 90-degree angle and your back knee is hovering above the floor.
Push off your front foot to bring your back foot forward, stepping into a lunge on the other side.
Position a barbell on your shoulders and stand in front of a box or bench.
Push your hips back and bend your knees to lower your body until your glutes touch the box.
Pause for a moment and then push your body back to the starting position.
Stand facing away from a bench, grab a pair of dumbbells and hold them at arm's length at your sides.
Place the toes of your left foot on the bench behind you.
Lower your body until your front knee is bent at least 90 degrees.
Pause, then push your body back to the starting position.
Stand upright with your hands at your hips.
Take a step forward with one foot and lower your body until your front knee is at a 90-degree angle and your back knee is hovering above the floor.
Push back up to the starting position and repeat with the other leg.
Stand holding a dumbbell close to your chest.
Squat down, keeping your chest up and your knees over your toes.
Push back up to the start position and repeat.
Stand with a barbell resting on your shoulders, your hands just wider than shoulder-width apart.
Squat down, keeping your chest up and your knees over your toes.
Push back up to the start position and repeat.
Sit on the machine with your back flat against the backrest.
Place your legs on the padded levers and hold onto the handles.
Squeeze your legs together against the resistance and then slowly return to the starting position.
Stand in front of a barbell secured in a landmine attachment, with the other end of the bar in both hands.
Position the bar at chest level with elbows bent.
Perform a squat, keeping your back straight and chest up.
Return to the start position and repeat.
Position yourself on a back extension station and hook your feet under the leg anchors.
Lower your upper body, bending at the hips, until your body is fully bent.
Raise your body by extending at the hips until your body forms a straight line.
Repeat the movement.
Stand holding a dumbbell in each hand with your feet hip-width apart.
Keep your arms straight and lift your shoulders as high as you can.
Pause, then slowly lower the weight back to the starting position.
Begin with a wide grip on the barbell, feet hip-width apart.
In a smooth motion, lift the barbell from the ground and up to overhead in one movement.
End with the barbell securely overhead with arms fully extended.
Return to the starting position and repeat.
Grasp the pull-up bar with a underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart.
Pull your body up until your chin is level with the bar, then slowly lower back to the start position.
Repeat the movement.
Place a barbell on the back of your shoulders and stand with your feet hip-width apart.
Bend at your hips and lower your torso until it is parallel to the floor.
Return to the starting position by extending your hips and repeat.
Set a bar at hip height and position yourself underneath it.
Grab the bar with an overhand grip and hang underneath it with your body straight.
Pull yourself up to the bar, then lower yourself back down and repeat.
Stand with your feet hip-width apart and hold a kettlebell in front of you with both hands at arm length.
Bend at your hips and knees and lower your torso until it forms a 45-degree angle to the floor.
Swing the kettlebell between your legs and then forward to the height of your shoulders and repeat.
Stand with feet hip-width apart and bend at the hips, keeping your back nearly parallel to the floor.
Grab the barbell with an overhand grip, hands just beyond shoulder width.
Pull the bar to your upper abdomen and then lower it back to the floor in a controlled manner.
Stand in a power rack with the barbell at knee level.
Bend at your hips and knees and grab the bar with an overhand grip.
Without allowing your lower back to round, stand up with the barbell and repeat.
Lie face down on a bench that is elevated off the ground.
Hold a barbell with a pronated grip and let it hang underneath you.
Pull the barbell up to your lower chest and squeeze your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement.
Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing out.
Bend at your hips and knees and grab the bar with an overhand grip.
Without allowing your lower back to round, pull your torso back and up, thrust your hips forward, and stand up with the barbell.
Load one side of a barbell and secure the other end in a corner.
Stand over the bar with one foot on each side, bend at the hips and knees, and grasp the bar near the weighted end.
Pull the bar to your upper abs.
Begin with the barbell on the ground and stand with your feet hip-width apart.
In one motion, clean the barbell to your shoulders.
Dip at the knees, then explosively push up with your legs as you press the barbell over your head.
Return the barbell to the ground safely and repeat.
Stand on an elevated platform and grab a barbell with an overhand grip.
Bend at your hips and knees, and pull the barbell up, keeping your chest up and your back straight.
Return the barbell back to the ground and repeat.
Sit on the ground with a bench behind you and a loaded barbell over your hips.
Lean back against the bench and drive your hips up by pressing your feet into the ground.
Lower your hips back to the ground and repeat.
Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart.
Place your hands behind your head so your thumbs are behind your ears.
Curl up and forward so that your head, neck, and shoulder blades lift off the floor.
Get into a plank position, hands planted directly under your shoulders, butt down, and your body a straight line from head to heels.
Pull your right knee into your chest as far as you can.
Switch legs, pulling one knee out and bringing the other knee in.
Adjust the seat and handles of the bike to fit your height.
Start pedaling at a steady pace.
Keep your back straight and hold the handles lightly.
Kneel on the floor and hold an Ab Wheel with both hands.
Roll the wheel forward, keeping your back straight, until you feel your abs stretch.
Roll the wheel back toward your knees to return to the starting position.
Sit at a lat pulldown station and grab the bar with one hand, palm facing forward.
Pull the bar down to your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body.
Slowly return the bar to the starting position.
Sit on the ground with a bench behind you and a loaded barbell over your hips.
Lean back against the bench and drive your hips up by pressing your feet into the ground.
Lower your hips back to the ground and repeat.
Sit on the machine with your feet firmly on the ground.
Grasp the cable handles with an underhand grip.
Curl the handles toward your shoulders, keeping your elbows still.
Slowly return the handles to the starting position.
Stand tall with your feet hip-width apart.
Start to jog slowly, landing softly on the balls of your feet.
Gradually increase your pace, swinging your arms in rhythm with your steps.
Lie down flat on the ground, arms fully extended above your head.
Engage your core to lift your upper body and legs off the ground at the same time, reaching for your toes.
Lower yourself back down with control.
Get into a high plank position. Place your hands close together, with your thumbs and index fingers touching to form a diamond shape.
Lower your body towards the floor while keeping your back flat and your hips in line with your shoulders.
Push back up to the start position.
Adjust the seat and handles of the bike to fit your height.
Start pedaling at a steady pace.
Keep your back straight and hold the handles lightly.
Stand with your feet hip-width apart. Place a barbell on the floor close to your shins.
Bend your knees and hips to take hold of the bar with an overhand grip.
In one swift movement, lift the barbell to your shoulders by extending your hips and knees.
Quickly bend your knees and hips to get under the bar as it rises, then stand up straight.
Lie on your back with your arms extended out to the sides, forming a T shape.
Bend your knees and drop them to one side, keeping your shoulders on the ground.
Hold this position for a few seconds, then switch sides.
Sit on the ground with one leg extended straight in front of you and the other leg bent.
Reach forward and try to touch your toes on the extended leg.
Hold this position for a few seconds, then switch legs.
Stand upright and grab your ankle or foot with one hand.
Pull your heel toward your glutes until you feel a stretch in the front of your thigh.
Hold this position for a few seconds, then switch legs.
Stand or sit upright and raise one arm overhead.
Bend the raised arm at the elbow so that your hand reaches towards the opposite shoulder blade.
Use your other hand to gently pull the elbow of the raised arm towards your head, feeling a stretch in your triceps.
Hold this position for a few seconds, then switch arms.
Start in a lunge position with one knee on the ground and the other leg forward, knee bent at a 90-degree angle.
Keep your upper body upright and push your hips forward until you feel a stretch in the front of your hip.
Hold this position for a few seconds, then switch legs.
Stand facing a wall and place your hands on the wall at shoulder height.
Step one foot back and keep it straight, pressing the heel into the ground.
Bend your front knee and lean forward, feeling a stretch in your calf.
Hold this position for a few seconds, then switch legs.
Sit on the ground with your knees bent and feet elevated slightly off the ground.
Lean back slightly to engage your core and twist your torso from side to side, touching the ground on each side with your hands.
Continue alternating sides in a controlled manner.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and toes pointing slightly outward.
Lower into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back.
Explosively jump up, reaching your arms overhead.
Land softly back into the squat position and repeat.
Grip the parallel dip bars with your palms facing inward and arms straight.
Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the ground.
Push through your palms to return to the starting position.
Grip the parallel dip bars with your palms facing inward and arms straight.
Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the ground.
Push through your palms to return to the starting position.
Start in a standing position with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Bend your knees and place your hands on the floor in front of you.
Kick your feet back into a plank position, perform a push-up, and then jump your feet back up towards your hands.
Explosively jump into the air, reaching your arms overhead.
Land softly and repeat the movement.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a medicine ball in both hands at chest level.
Raise the ball overhead, then forcefully slam it onto the ground in front of you.
Squat down to pick up the ball and repeat the movement.
